It is more than a cliche to say something about energy conservation.
 A lot of countries established a regulation that encourage companies to
 put Energy Star Level or a similar metric on each appliance that they made.
 Consumers carefully consider this metric when they want to buy a new appliance.
 Beside of the regulation, in addition, consumers' preference to energy
 efficient appliances is a driving force for companies to develop more energy
 efficient appliances than before.
 People's awareness of energy conservation grows rapidly as developing countries
 keep consuming tremendous amount of fossil fuel as they are developing
 rapidly.
 Public policy strongly encourage people to be aware of lack of fossil fuel
 and improve their energy efficiency for the world to be sustainable.
 NGOs also keep eyes on companies to determine their sustainability.
 A good and compelling example is the great success of Toyota's Prius hybrid
 automobile.
 Due to its high price, it may not be cost effective for a short period
 of time.
 But a lot of people are willing to buy one if they are capable.
 That means as long as cost doesn't exceed a lot more than a traditional
 solution, some of them may still buy those products based upon their altruism.
 All those could be strong motivations for us to develeop our system.
 Meaning we have certain places where we sell our ideas.
 
\end_layout

