Sensing of Human Activity
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 such as sensory grammer and activity zone focus on the fact that what is
 the most typical or common mobility profile when people do a specific behavior.
 And they can achieve more than 90% of accuracy of detection rate under
 realistic settings.
 However, this approach doesn't actually care of how people change an environmen
t when people do a specific job except their movement profile.
 For example, in the activity zone paper they simply assume that if a person
 is moving toward and backward in front of a white board, she is writing/using
 the white board.
 However, it is always possible that there is a case where she is just thinking
 and going toward and backward in front of the white boards.
 Imagine if we can also monitor current status of the white board, say accelerat
ion/vibration.
 Such information, of course, helps distinguish this kind of ambiguity.
 However, adding sensing modality often is not desired as a cost issue come
 to the place.
 So, we also consider tradeoff between adding sensing modality and detection
 rate.
 One interesting observation regarding this issue could be [] where the
 detection rate is a bell shaped curve due to various noise sources.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Recalling our focus of work, we are aiming at monitoring people and sources
 of resources at the same time.
 Therefore, our approach is, in that regard, new because the correlation
 among users and resources is the most important and essential point of
 view.
 Say, how people interact with appliances, how people change the status
 of appliances, how different depending upon individual's characteristics
 and how appliances can differentiate people.
 Therefore, the interesting features could be both of people and appliances.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We envision that our work can be an initial step to a new sensing regime
 that scales down to the individual level of granularity.
 Except some information that is solely personal such as health monitoring,
 there are very few attempts to provide individual level of granularity
 of sensory information.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Interaction models played an important role especially in the Human Computer
 Interface regime.
 Some of researchers developed several techniques that accomodate users
 with a new and intuitive way to interact with machines.
 For example, a well known mice, touch pad, and other input devices gave
 users a great experience from the beginning and they are all around nowadays.
 As computing resources play an important role in our daily life, people
 started to look at various aspects of technology.
 Especially they started to want machines to help their decision making
 processes by providing suggestions, numbers in regards to performance,
 health, and money, and personal stories.
 Such demands initiated tremendous amounts of research areas such as artificial
 intelligence, personal health monitoring, and others.
 In similar regards, we are aiming at develeoping a system that provides
 personal stories in terms of resource/electricity consumption of individual
 level of granularity and therefore helping people improve their daily resource
 consumption pattern.
